        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-01-17T10:55:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1957-01-17T10:55:00-05:00" n="26"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d26">
                <head>26. Memorandum of a Conversation Between the <gloss type="from"
                        >President</gloss> and the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>,
                    White House, Washington, January 17, 1957,10:55 a.m.<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d26fn1">Source: Eisenhower Library, Dulles Papers, Meetings with the
                        President. Secret; Personal and Private. Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_DAW1">Dulles</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" type="conversation-or-meeting-date"
                            when="1957-01-17T10:55:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 17, 1957,10:55 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[Here follows discussion of unrelated subjects.]</p>
                <p>I discussed with the President the Suez situation and the difficulty of bringing
                    about a satisfactory result in view of the fact that most of the pressures and
                    “carrots” were in our hands whereas <persName corresp="#p_HD1"
                        >Hammarskjold</persName> was doing the negotiation. The President wondered
                    whether the time might not be right to ask <persName corresp="#p_ARB1">Bob
                        Anderson</persName> to go back again to Cairo. I said we were thinking that
                        <persName corresp="#p_HD1">Hammarskjold</persName> should go and we did not
                    want to cut across his negotiations or seem to be working behind his back. We
                    then briefly considered the possibility that <persName corresp="#p_ARB1"
                        >Anderson</persName> might be in Cairo on a covert basis while <persName
                        corresp="#p_HD1">Hammarskjold</persName> was there and that their two
                    efforts might be coordinated.</p>
                <p>I said that <persName corresp="#p_LHCJ1">Lodge</persName> would be here tomorrow
                    at Cabinet meeting and that we were planning to talk with him about the
                        <persName corresp="#p_HD1">Hammarskjold</persName> plans.</p>
                <p>[Here follows discussion of unrelated subjects.]</p>
            </div>
